<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0de18f58-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s3986"><num value="3986">§ 3986.</num><heading> Submission of applications</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each applicant within a State which desires to receive a grant under this part shall submit the application prepared in accordance with <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s3985">section 3985 of this title</ref> to the State agency on <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002157">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002157"><num>1</num> So in original. Probably should be “for”.</note> higher education or the State educational agency, as the case may be, for approval and shall submit the approved application to the Secretary under <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s3985">section 3985 of this title</ref>. Each such application shall be submitted jointly by the local educational agency in the case of activities described in <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s3984/a">section 3984(a) of this title</ref>, or an institution of higher education in the case of activities described in <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s3984/b">section 3984(b) of this title</ref>, and each business concern or other party that is to participate in the program for which assistance is sought.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0de18f59-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/377/tIII/s307">Pub. L. 98–377, title III, § 307</ref>, <date date="1984-08-11">Aug. 11, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/1286">98 Stat. 1286</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/159/tII/s231">Pub. L. 99–159, title II, § 231</ref>, <date date="1985-11-22">Nov. 22, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/900">99 Stat. 900</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/100/418/tVI/s6031/b/2">Pub. L. 100–418, title VI, § 6031(b)(2)</ref>, <date date="1988-08-23">Aug. 23, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/1483">102 Stat. 1483</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
